paragraphs.text:
%spark
import spark.implicits._
import java.sql.Timestamp
import java.sql.Date
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat

case class WeatherData(
    idWeatherStation: String,
    idWeatherNcei: String,
    dateString: String,
    dateDate: java.sql.Date,
    dateTimestamp: java.sql.Timestamp,
    flag: String,
    latitude: String,
    longitude: String,
    surfaceObsType: String,
    elevationHeight: String,
    callLetterId: String,
    qualityProcess: String,
    windObsDirectionAngle: String,
    windObsDirectionQualityCode: String,
    windObsTypeCode: String,
    windObsSpeedRate: Integer,
    windObsSpeedQualityCode: String,
    skyObsCeilingHeight: Integer,
    skyObsCeilingQualityCode: String, 
    skyObsCeilingDeterminationCode: String,
    skyObsCavokCode: String,
    visibilityObsDistanceDim: Integer,
    visibilityObsDistanceQualityCode: String,
    visibilityObsVariabilityCode: String,
    visibilityObsQualityVariaCode: String,
    airTemp: Double,
    airTempObsQualityCode: String,
    airTempObsDewPointTemp: String,
    airTempObsDewPointQualityCode: String,
    atmosObsSeaLevelPressure: Integer,
    atmosObsSeaLevelPresQualityCode: String
    
    
    ) {
     override def toString(): String = "IdWeatherStation: "+idWeatherStation;
}
val format = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyyMMddHHmm")
val lines = sc.textFile("/Users/user/Documents/GitHub/Weather-Spark/weatherData/*")
val weatherRDD = lines.map(line => new WeatherData(
                                                    line.substring(4,10),
                                                    line.substring(10,15),
                                                    line.substring(15,27),
                                                    new Date(format.parse(line.substring(15,27)).getTime()),
                                                    new Timestamp(format.parse(line.substring(15,27)).getTime()),
                                                    line.substring(27,28),
                                                    line.substring(28,34),
                                                    line.substring(34,41),
                                                    line.substring(41,46),
                                                    line.substring(46,51),
                                                    line.substring(51,56),
                                                    line.substring(56,60),
                                                    line.substring(60,63),
                                                    line.substring(63,64),
                                                    line.substring(64,65),
                                                    Integer.valueOf(line.substring(65,69)),
                                                    line.substring(69,70),
                                                    Integer.valueOf(line.substring(70,75)),
                                                    line.substring(75,76),
                                                    line.substring(76,77),
                                                    line.substring(77,78),
                                                    Integer.valueOf(line.substring(78,84)),
                                                    line.substring(84,85),
                                                    line.substring(85,86),
                                                    line.substring(86,87),
                                                    line.substring(87,92).toDouble,
                                                    line.substring(92,93),
                                                    line.substring(93,98),
                                                    line.substring(98,99),
                                                    Integer.valueOf(line.substring(99,104)),
                                                    line.substring(104,105)
                                                    ))
val df = weatherRDD.toDF()

df.show()
df.registerTempTable("weatherData")

paragraphs.title: Wind speed
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select dateDate, 
    min(windObsSpeedRate) as min,
    max(windObsSpeedRate) as max,
    avg(windObsSpeedRate) as average 
    from weatherData
    where dateDate > ${startDate='2013-01-01'}
    and dateDate < ${endDate='2013-12-31'}
    and  idWeatherStation == ${idWeatherStation='010460'}
    and windObsSpeedRate < 9999 
    group by dateDate 
    order by dateDate
